#TrackNigeria Following disagreement between the leader of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN), Sheikh Ibrahim El-Zakzaky and the management of the hospital to which he and his wife were taken for treatment in New Delhi, India, the Sheikh has confirmed that the hospital management has communicated that they return to Nigeria. PRNigeria gathered that El-Zakzaky and his entourage departed New Delhi in a commercial airline at 5pm Nigerian time today. In a video message sent through his office, the Sheikh said it was decided that they would be flown back to Nigeria. He prayed that may that be the best option in the circumstances. A top member of of Islamic Human Right Commission (IHRC) which negoatiated the medical treatment in India said that the Nigerian government’s interference and scuttling of the whole process rather than supervision as ordered by the court is the direct cause of the impasse. By PRNigeria …As Indian govt gives him ultimatum to return to NigeriaFacts have just emerged that the leader of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN), Sheikh Ibrahim El-Zakzaky has refused to receive treatment from unknown doctors that had been provided to treat him in India, different from those billed and booked to… August 14, 2019 In "Featured" …begins  treatment with his choice doctorsReports from India indicates that the hospital has agreed to the request of Sheikh Ibrahim El-Zakzaky to use known and choice doctors that will treat him. In a new videotape made available to PRNigeria, the representative of Islamic Human Right Commission (IHRC) said the issue… August 14, 2019 In "Featured" The leader of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN), Sheikh Ibrahim El-Zakzaky will depart Nigeria Monday evening through the Abuja International Airport to India. A source, who disclosed this to Newsdiaryonline in a telephone conversation said El-Zakzaky will depart with his wife, Zeenat for the Medenta Hospital, New Delhi, India… August 12, 2019 In "Featured"